author: Karen DeYoung
title: Foreign policy challenges persist for a distracted U.S. in the midst of pandemic
description: Allies say that Washington's preoccuption with the domestic challenge of coronavirus has undermined its role as a global leader, and adversaries have sought to take advantage.
content:
The administrations ability to manage these issues, preserving U.S. interests even as its attention and resources are sapped by the domestic pandemic fight, will help determine the starting point for its post-virus position in the world.
